      "author_name": "Gokul Krishna",
      "rating": 1,
      "review_text": "I admitted my wife at Sparsh Hospital, Yeshwanthpur for just one day due to acute gastroenteritis with dehydration (a basic illness). The hospital shocked us with a gross bill of ₹60,535, gave an “MOU discount” of ₹8,298, and finally charged ₹52,857 net.\n\nThis included:\n•\t₹12,500 for private room\n•\t₹22,000+ for basic blood tests which are normally inexpensive\n•\t₹300 per day parking charge outsourced to a private vendor\n\nFor a simple one-day illness, this bill is unbelievable and unjustifiable.\n\nWhile insurance covered most of it, I wonder how middle-class and poor families can ever afford this kind of treatment. Hospitals should heal patients, not exploit them with inflated bills and hidden charges.\n\nIf there was an option for negative rating, I would have definitely given it.",
      "review_time": "2025-09-16T04:07:44Z"
    },
