      "review_text": "Very Disappointed with Emergency Care at Sparsh Hospital – 27th August 2025\nI had a terrible experience at Sparsh Hospital yesterday, and I feel compelled to share it. In the early morning hours of 27th August 2025, around 3:00 AM, I was suffering from severe hemorrhoid pain. Despite taking a painkiller, the pain didn’t subside, and I couldn’t sleep—so I visited the emergency section, expecting at least basic compassion and professionalism.\nInstead, I was met with shocking rudeness from the duty doctor. He behaved as if I was disturbing his sleep and spoke to me in a completely unprofessional and disrespectful manner. His exact words were along the lines of, “What do you want? Why have you come here?” – delivered in a harsh and dismissive tone.\nAs a regular visitor to this hospital who has trusted it for my family’s healthcare needs, this behavior was both unacceptable and deeply disappointing. Emergency care should be a place where patients are treated with urgency and respect—not made to feel like a burden for seeking help.\nI sincerely hope the hospital management takes this issue seriously. No patient deserves to be treated like this, especially when they are in pain and vulnerable.",
