      "author_name": "kshama",
      "rating": 1,
      "review_text": "A BIG NO!!!\nI had recommended this hospital for my niece’s treatment solely because my trusted doctor practices here. I have complete faith in his medical judgment and treatment approach.\n\nHowever, the overall billing experience has left me extremely disappointed. We had specifically opted for a triple-sharing room expecting affordability, but were shocked by the final bill—especially the charges listed under ‘laboratory services’. The prices for several tests were 3–4 times higher than those at equally reputed diagnostic centers outside.\n\nWhat was even more disheartening was the complete lack of transparency—there was no prior communication or estimate provided regarding these charges. The final bill came as an unpleasant surprise. It’s disconcerting that even after selecting the most economical room category, the hospital manages to inflate costs through excessive diagnostic pricing.\n\nAt the very least, patients and their families deserve honest and transparent billing practices. When the hospital was new the prices also were very competent. But now it's a rip off. I sincerely urge the hospital management to review this issue and take corrective action.\n\nTo add, I was recently contacted by the hospital to ask whether I would recommend their services. My answer was an emphatic no. My trust remains solely with my Dr Mahesh Pai. Wherever he practices is where I will go in future.",
